            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">  The cost is minimal, and provides a modern experience for working with diagnostics.\n\nIt does interfere with other functions using the quickfix list. Say you use `lsp.buf.references()` with the intention of going through all of them to change the calls to a different function. You'd jump to the first location, make a change, get new diagnostics and lose the references in the quickfix list.\n\nIf this gets added it imho shouldn't be on by default as it would be too invasive and kind of a breaking change.\nAnd if it gets added by default and you've to turn it on - it raises the question why include it if adding it only requires the few lines you posted.\n ",
