            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Fair. We could also use the loclist for this (as I feel this is used less often than the qflist), although that would probably have the same problem. Another option is to just add this example to the docs. The example given does have some rough edges (pretty much the same as #30868), but works great for people that only want to use the qflist for diagnostics.\n\nCounterargument: if it's available from core, plugins and diagnostic providers can use the handler without implementing themself in slightly different ways.\n\nCountercounterargument: also trivial to implement for these plugins or providers.",
