        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Sounds attractive to me. Waiting for comments / objections.\n> I think the show function is called on DiagnosticChanged, thus this would update the qflist when the list of diagnostics changes. The cost is minimal, and provides a modern experience for working with diagnostics.\n\nAlso OP mentioned in the original post that it is minimal cost, i would like to say f*ck no it is not, doing this ` vim.diagnostic.setqflist({ open = false })` on each diagnostics event is not cheap at all. Re-creating the diagnostic items on the main thread, the qflist items every damn time, is not zero or minimal cost, especially if linked to workspace diagnostics and not document diagnostics.\n\nThere might be an argument here for a separate diagnostics ui window or ui element, separate from qf list in the future. There are other lsp features like the call graph, which are not suitable for qf list as well. ",
