        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thanks for the feedback. no one said it should be done on the main thread. Also, isn't this exactly what the sign, virtual_line and underline handlers do? I don't think `setqflist` is computationally much heavier than setting signs, virtual lines and underlines. A separate diagnostics ui element is indeed a good suggestion, but that has a much higher complexity than this simple addition. I'm aware not everything will use or like this feature, that's why I already suggested it could be opt-in.\n\nI could throw in a `vim.schedule` in the [example docs PR](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31371) if you prefer that.",
